## 📦 backupbuddy

`backupbuddy.sh` is a smart Bash-based backup tool for Linux users. It allows you to back up files or directories with optional versioning, and custom destination support — all from your terminal.

---

## 🚀 Features

- ✅ Back up any file or directory
- 📁 Save backups to a custom destination
- 🕓 Automatically timestamped archive filenames
- 🔖 Version count display
- 🧼 Clean, user-friendly command-line interface

---

## 🛠️ Dependencies

To use all features, ensure the following are installed:

- `bash` (usually preinstalled)
- `tar`

---

## 📂 Compatibility

Tested on:

Debian 12 (Bookworm)
Most Linux distributions with Bash 4+

📦 Usage
./backupbuddy.sh -s <source> -d <destination> [-v] [-h]

---

## 🔧 Options

Option	Description
-s	Path to the source file or directory (required)
-d	Path to the destination directory (required)
-v	Show version info (optional)
-h	Show help message

---

## 📌 Example
./backupbuddy.sh -s ~/Documents/report.pdf -d ~/Backups
This will create a compressed backup of report.pdf in the ~/Backups directory.

